item.title: SpaceLab Launch
item.description: Photo Credit: NASA/Aubrey Gemignani The project SpaceLab is a school program at the Singapore American School. The program allows students to create a space experiment that will be sent to the international space station for one month. This is the second year of the program. A team of eleven students including me created a experiment that seeks to test the effect of micro-gravity on electro-plating copper.
